textAfterTable: 16 canciones Biografía Nacido(a): 05 de agosto de 1904 en Paris, KY Género: Jazz Años de actividad: '20s, '30s, '40s, '50s, '60s, '70s, '80s A mellow-toned swing trumpeter with a distinctive sound and a lyrical style, Bill Coleman was a consistent if never particularly famous musician. In 1927, he went to New York with Cecil and Lloyd Scott's band, with whom he made his recording debut. He worked with Luis Russell (1929-1932) and Charlie Johnson, and then in 1933 traveled to France with Lucky Millinder.
